Author: Martasoloviy
Title: ğŸ“Œ [ANN] ğŸ“ˆ [Pre-ICO] ğŸš€ Morpheus.Network - Automated Global Supply Chain ğŸŒ
Body: Morpheus Network is an all-new blockchain solution that aims to remove many of the complexities that underlie the supply chain process. For example, when a document needs to be shared with multiple institutions, it can be uploaded directly onto the native blockchain where it can be viewed by multiple partiesâ€” but cannot be tampered with or inadvertently altered.

Author: Martasoloviy
Title: ğŸ“Œ [ANN] ğŸ“ˆ [Pre-ICO] ğŸš€ Morpheus.Network - Automated Global Supply Chain ğŸŒ
Body: In short, Morpheus Network is able to provide a high level of automation within existing supply chains is by deploying smart contracts. These allow for the execution of predetermined, automated work contracts as well as enable streamlined international payments as per prearranged financial terms between all of the involved actors.

Author: Martasoloviy
Title: ğŸ“Œ [ANN] ğŸ“ˆ [Pre-ICO] ğŸš€ Morpheus.Network - Automated Global Supply Chain ğŸŒ
Body: Additionally, the platform can be fully integrated with Waltonchain (WTC), a unique blockchain service that is compatible with technologies such as RFID tags, Sia and helps verify the transfer of data as a single object within a supply chain.

Author: Martasoloviy
Title: ğŸ“Œ [ANN] ğŸ“ˆ [Pre-ICO] ğŸš€ Morpheus.Network - Automated Global Supply Chain ğŸŒ
Body: From a monetary perspective, Morpheus enables suppliers, manufacturers and exporters to send and receive money across 200 nations using their local fiat currency. This is made possible through the use of SWIFT transfers that are currently popular all around the world.

Title: ğŸ“Œ [ANN] ğŸ“ˆ [Pre-ICO] ğŸš€ Morpheus.Network - Automated Global Supply Chain ğŸŒ
Body: Our current development has been based on Ethereum's blockchain for the Smart Contract technology. In spite of that, we are keeping the development platform agnostic. So, in case Ethereum's scalability issues aren't resolved, we could migrate to another blockchain.  Our view is to be platform agnostic wherein we can leverage different platforms for their inherent strengths. Being platform agnostic allows us (if necessary) to migrate to another blockchain such as EOS, NEO, Cardano or NEM in the future.  We also are leveraging other blockchain technologies, such as Stellar, for different aspects of the system, and utilizing them as side chains.

Body: Frequently Asked Questions   What's the softcap, hardcap, and circulation supply? â­ï¸ Soft cap: 1.8 million USD      Hard cap: 36 million USD      20,000,000 for Token presale (for circulating supply)      52,000,000 for Token sale (for circulating supply)  What Is The Minimum And Maximum Contributions For The Token Sale? â­ï¸ The minimum contributions per investor for the presale is 0.1 ETH. When does the KYC process start? â­ï¸ Shortly after a contribution is made, you will receive an email with details on KYC verification.  What happens if I fail the KYC process after making a contribution? â­ï¸ You will get a few opportunities to pass KYC (supply additional documentation if required etc.) If KYC repeatedly fails we will have to return contribution.  Any gas and gwei recommendations? â­ï¸ 200.000 gas 40-60 gwei. If someone submits a transaction with gas PRICE over 60 GWEI, it will fail. Can I transfer MORPH tokens to MEW? â­ï¸ Distribution of tokens takes place 28 days after the main sale concludes. Your tokens will be transferrable to your ETH wallet right after that.

Author: Morpheus Network Official
Title: ğŸ“Œ [ANN] ğŸ“ˆ [Pre-ICO] ğŸš€ Morpheus.Network - Automated Global Supply Chain ğŸŒ
Body: Morpheus Network aims to optimize the supply chain and decentralize the global trade industry. And for that to be made possible, the platform integrates a cryptocurrency payment system which utilizes blockchain technology. We recognize blockchain as a technology to be leveraged across supply chains to see breakthroughs in automation, optimization, security, visibility and forecasting. Automation is achieved utilizing Smart Contracts, driving the supply chain with predetermined, automated work contracts, shipping & customs documents as well as automated international payments.  The layering of other Blockchain technologies, as a part of , or an objective in the Smart Contract, is another key feature further enabling supply chain automation.  This involves the integration with other blockchains such as using the Walton Blockchain to signify the arrival of a shipment with an RFID scan, or using Sia to verify the transfer of data as a single objective in a supply chain Smart Contract. We believe that Morpheus Network can truly revolutionize the global trade industry, and bridge the inefficiency gaps in the global supply chain.

Author: Morpheus Network Official
Title: ğŸ“Œ [ANN] ğŸ“ˆ [Pre-ICO] ğŸš€ Morpheus.Network - Automated Global Supply Chain ğŸŒ
Body: The Morpheus executive team and developers are based primarily in Canada, Taiwan and India with the company registered in Seychelles. Our team and advisors are distributed around the globe in countries including United States, Russia, Japan, Philippines, Singapore and Belarus. We have a strategic partnership with WINJIT and they are handeling a huge part of our development currently with 15 developers working on our project. We don't have all 15 developers listed on our site, but a few key individuals. It is a close relationship - daily contact through a private Slack channel, with multiple videos calls every week, etc. I'd like you to check the team members' LinkedIn profiles, in case you have any doubts/queries. Thanks a lot for this question

Author: Morpheus Network Official
Title: ğŸ“Œ [ANN] ğŸ“ˆ [Pre-ICO] ğŸš€ Morpheus.Network - Automated Global Supply Chain ğŸŒ
Body: We've been asked many times by the community what makes Morpheus.Network different than the other projects on the market? Let me preface that any of these other blockchain technologies or ICOs are all great companies and ideas, and the Morpheus.Network is just a completely different platform.  Also, given the success of any given technology, we would look into integrating that blockchain as a â€œsidechainâ€ as a part of a Morpheus Network Smart Contract.  The Morpheus Network is designed to be utilized by the global trade, or import/export industry.  That is how the platformâ€™s automation features are designed including the methods of payment transfers offered by the Morpheus Network to drive the 15 trillion dollar global trade industry  Origin Trail â€“ This is another amazing concept.  Similar elements in the use of blockchain to record, maintain and source the origin of where globally shipped goods come from.  Completely different without any elements of a payment system or automating supply chain.  ShipChain & IMMLA  â€“ These are 2 great companies and teams.  Trucking and multiple transportation services blockchain technologies but very different since no automating supply chain with a global payment system.  Sweet Bridge â€“ They really have an amazing site with an extremely knowledgeable team.  They have a heavy focus on lending funds based on onesâ€™ assets, which is a great platform, but much different than our platformâ€™s model of automating processes in a supply chain as objectives in a Smart Contract.   CargoX - Another awesome project. Their concentration on the document generation and sharing between parties is a Morpheus.Network feature as well. The Morpheus platform has more document generation capabilities (work contracts and more) as well as the means to execute these contracts as a part of an automated Smart Contract. Along with our payment system, it really sets us apart  TenX / Monetha / other payment systems â€“  There are so many crypto based payment systems with talented and motivated teams.  Their business models are heavily focused on the retail market.  For buying a set of headphones or a coffee at a cafe, they may be better options.   Eximchain - Another wonderful project, but our payment system is multilayered allowing different payment flow possibilities. Also, our project is dealing with supply chain inefficiencies by focusing more on automating the global trade system.  Once again we love these projects and we fully believe in interoperability between technologies to fully optimize the global supply chain and the success of the Morpheus.Network can be parallel to their success, and not in competition with it.

Author: Morpheus Network Official
Title: ğŸ“Œ [ANN] ğŸ“ˆ [Pre-ICO] ğŸš€ Morpheus.Network - Automated Global Supply Chain ğŸŒ
Body: We've been asked many times by the community what makes Morpheus.Network different than the other projects on the market? Let me preface that any of these other blockchain technologies or ICOs are all great companies and ideas, and the Morpheus.Network is just a completely different platform.  Also, given the success of any given technology, we would look into integrating that blockchain as a â€œsidechainâ€ as a part of a Morpheus Network Smart Contract.  The Morpheus Network is designed to be utilized by the global trade, or import/export industry.  That is how the platformâ€™s automation features are designed including the methods of payment transfers offered by the Morpheus Network to drive the 15 trillion dollar global trade industry  Origin Trail â€“ This is another amazing concept.  Similar elements in the use of blockchain to record, maintain and source the origin of where globally shipped goods come from.  Completely different without any elements of a payment system or automating supply chain.  ShipChain & IMMLA  â€“ These are 2 great companies and teams.  Trucking and multiple transportation services blockchain technologies but very different since no automating supply chain with a global payment system.  Sweet Bridge â€“ They really have an amazing site with an extremely knowledgeable team.  They have a heavy focus on lending funds based on onesâ€™ assets, which is a great platform, but much different than our platformâ€™s model of automating processes in a supply chain as objectives in a Smart Contract.   CargoX - Another awesome project. Their concentration on the document generation and sharing between parties is a Morpheus.Network feature as well. The Morpheus platform has more document generation capabilities (work contracts and more) as well as the means to execute these contracts as a part of an automated Smart Contract. Along with our payment system, it really sets us apart  TenX / Monetha / other payment systems â€“  There are so many crypto based payment systems with talented and motivated teams.  Their business models are heavily focused on the retail market.  For buying a set of headphones or a coffee at a cafe, they may be better options.   Eximchain - Another wonderful project, but our payment system is multilayered allowing different payment flow possibilities. Also, our project is dealing with supply chain inefficiencies by focusing more on automating the global trade system.  Once again we love these projects and we fully believe in interoperability between technologies to fully optimize the global supply chain and the success of the Morpheus.Network can be parallel to their success, and not in competition with it.

Body: Actually, the initial large challenge was selecting the proper ERP system for the backend of the Morpheus.Network. We had extensive meetings with multiple software implementation firms along with advisor from SWIFT, Will Liu to make the proper decision. Microsoft Dynamics 365 ERP was selected because of its flexibility with the functions of the Morpheus.Network platform, but also for its seamless integration to the SWIFT payment hub.  The ERP (dynamics) is connected to the SWIFT hub directly.  The necessary info is passed onto SWIFT to use their messaging service to initiate a settlement.

Author: Morpheus Network Official
Title: ğŸ“Œ [ANN] ğŸ“ˆ [Pre-ICO] ğŸš€ Morpheus.Network - Automated Global Supply Chain ğŸŒ
Body: Dear Community, some exciting news to share with you! Morpheus.Network is pleased and excited to announce that we have joined the Blockchain in Transport Alliance (BiTA)!  BiTA is a consortium of the foremost leaders in the freight industry forging a path towards industry standards in blockchain use. Their members include industry leaders including FedEx, UPS, SAP, Penske, JD Logistics, Salesforce, and many more. Their goal is to bring together leading companies in the freight technology industries that have a vested interest in the development of blockchain technology.  In addition to establishing market standards, the organization is focused on engaging with the industry and providing educational resources to ensure the full potential of the benefits of blockchain technology is carried through.  We look forward to working closely with other members to help lead, develop and embrace a common framework and standards as well as promote blockchain technologies in the logistics industry. https://bita.studio/

Body: We integrate, in our opinion, the best crypto payment system as a part of an automated supply chain system. Our SWIFT integration allows us to send payments directly into the bank accounts of your suppliers as part of a Smart Contract. The payments can also be purely as crypto payments as well without using the traditional banking system as well. Advantages to using the various payment methods depending on your company's structure.  Original digital document generation (contracts, shipping and customs docs, etc.) are also automated objectives in the Smart Contract. We also are layering other blockchain (such as Walton for RFID scans and Sia or Storj for storage) and non-blockchain technologies (integration with shipping company tracking info as Smart Contract objectives) to drive Global Trade.
